<subSubSection id="C33459D4FFB13D11FF3CCC3CFEB3FADB" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B910A5FFFB13D11FF3CCC3CFDDEFCD0" blockId="9.[182,578,849,876]" box="[182,578,849,876]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<heading id="D0D9BD33FFB13D11FF3CCC3CFDDEFCD0" box="[182,578,849,876]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FF3CCC3CFDDEFCD0" authority="(Toula, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Toula" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[182,578,849,876]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Dihoplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pikermiensis">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FF3CCC3CFE39FCD0" bold="true" box="[182,421,849,876]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Dihoplus pikermiensis</emphasis>
(Toula, 1906)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B910A5FFFB13D11FFFBCCFCFEB3FADB" blockId="9.[111,648,913,1700]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
The best specimen is skull FM-2469, which is complete but with a bone surface that is heavily eroded and fragmented (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FEA0CCBDFDA1FC57" author="GERAADS D. &amp; SPASSOV N." box="[298,573,976,1003]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="99 - 122" refId="ref19501" refString="GERAADS D. &amp; SPASSOV N. 2009. - Rhinocerotidae from the late Miocene of Bulgaria. Palaeontographica A, 287: 99 - 122." type="journal article" year="2009">Geraads &amp; Spassov 2009</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2, pl. 1, G, H). It clearly displays all the features by which the skull of this species can be distinguished from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FF65CB42FD1BFBF6" authority="(Osborn, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Osborn" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[239,647,1071,1098]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Ceratotherium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neumayri">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FF65CB42FE7DFBF5" box="[239,481,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Ceratotherium neumayri</emphasis>
(Osborn, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FFFCCB22FE91FBD6" author="GERAADS D." box="[118,269,1103,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="13 - 41" refId="ref19318" refString="GERAADS D. 1988. - Revision des Rhinocerotidae (Mammalia) du Turolien de Pikermi. Comparaison avec les formes voisines. Annales de Paleontologie 74: 13 - 41." type="journal article" year="1988">Geraads 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FE93CB22FDB9FBD6" author="GERAADS D. &amp; SPASSOV N." box="[281,549,1103,1130]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="99 - 122" refId="ref19501" refString="GERAADS D. &amp; SPASSOV N. 2009. - Rhinocerotidae from the late Miocene of Bulgaria. Palaeontographica A, 287: 99 - 122." type="journal article" year="2009">Geraads &amp; Spassov 2009</bibRefCitation>
), such as the sharp ventral orbital border, the shortened cranial basis with the post-tympanic overlapping the post-glenoid process, and a constricted protocone on the molars. The rarely preserved premaxillae are complete, and show no trace of incisors. Such incisors are large in its likely ancestor 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FE44CA63FE9FFAF4" authority="(Kaup, 1832)" baseAuthorityName="Kaup" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Dihoplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schleiermacheri">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FE44CA63FD1BFA9B" box="[462,647,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">D. schleiermacheri</emphasis>
(Kaup, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
, and may still occasionally be found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FF07CA20FEB4FADA" baseAuthorityName="Toula" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[141,296,1356,1382]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Dihoplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pikermiensis">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FF07CA20FEB4FADA" box="[141,296,1356,1382]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">D. pikermiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33459D4FFB13D11FF02CA01FCA7FE6D" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B910A5FFFB13D11FF02CA01FE83F9F9" blockId="9.[111,648,913,1700]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
The mandible FM-2470, found close to the skull and probably belonging to the same individual, has a straight ventral border, unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FE4ACAC1FDA3FA79" baseAuthorityName="Osborn" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[448,575,1452,1478]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Ceratotherium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neumayri">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FE4ACAC1FDA3FA79" box="[448,575,1452,1478]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">C. neumayri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and a pair of large incisors (
<figureCitation id="131516DAFFB13D11FEDCCAA6FE37FA5A" box="[342,427,1483,1510]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="6.[113,123,1589,1606]" captionTargetBox="[126,1161,221,1550]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[569,1027,571,935]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIG. 3. — Fossil mammals from the Miocene of Strumyani (SW Bulgaria): A-C,?Tetralophodon atticus (Wagner,1857); A, DP2 FM-2027, occlusal view;B, dp2 FM-2799, lingual view,C, DP3 FM-2798,occlusal view; D, Dihoplus pikermiensis (Toula, 1906), dorsal view of symphysis FM-2470;E, Microstonyx major (Gervais,1848),maxilla FM-2801;F, G, Dorcatherium cf.puyhauberti Arambourg &amp; Piveteau,1929, mandible FM-2741 in occlusal (F)and lateral (G) views;H, Palaeotragus rouenii Gaudry,1861,mandible FM-2778;I, Miotragocerus (Pikermicerus) gaudryi (Kretzoi,1941), mandible FM-2103; J, Cervidae gen.et sp. indet., mandible FM-2100. Scale bar: A-C,F-J, 7.5 cm; D, 30 cm; E, 10 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5381384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5381384/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
), much smaller than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FF07CA86FED8F9B9" baseAuthorityName="Kaup" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[141,324,1515,1541]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Dihoplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schleiermacheri">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FF07CA86FED8F9B9" box="[141,324,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">D. schleiermacheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but less reduced than in other specimens of 
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FE83C966FE2BF998" box="[265,439,1546,1572]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FE83C966FE2FF998" baseAuthorityName="Toula" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[265,435,1546,1572]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Dihoplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pikermiensis">D. pikermiensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Measurements are given in 
<tableCitation id="C6AC3FE4FFB13D11FF41C947FE87F9F9" box="[203,283,1578,1605]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="10.[112,123,220,237]" captionText="TABLE 2. — Measurements (in mm) of Rhinocerotidae Gray, 1821 mandibles from the Miocene of Strumyani (SW Bulgaria). *, length of pre-dental portion; C., Ceratotherium; D., Dihoplus." pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B910A5FFFB13D11FF02C927FCA7FE6D" blockId="9.[111,648,913,1700]" lastBlockId="9.[674,1211,216,465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
In 
<collectingCountry id="F3394ACFFFB13D11FF2CC927FF63F9D9" box="[166,255,1610,1637]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E71DCFFB13D11FE81C926FE3BF9D8" baseAuthorityName="Toula" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[267,423,1610,1636]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinocerotidae" genus="Dihoplus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pikermiensis">
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FE81C926FE3BF9D8" box="[267,423,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">D. pikermiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also present at Kalimantsi and common at Hadjidimovo. It is also quite common in its type-locality, Pikermi, and has also been described from several other Turolian localities of the Aegean region (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FC50CF95FBEDFEAF" author="GERAADS D." box="[986,1137,248,275]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="13 - 41" refId="ref19318" refString="GERAADS D. 1988. - Revision des Rhinocerotidae (Mammalia) du Turolien de Pikermi. Comparaison avec les formes voisines. Annales de Paleontologie 74: 13 - 41." type="journal article" year="1988">Geraads 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FBF6CF95FB29FEAF" author="GERAADS D." box="[1148,1205,248,275]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="81 - 95" refId="ref19350" refString="GERAADS D. 1994. - Les gisements de Mammiferes du Miocene superieur de Kemiklitepe, Turquie. 4. Rhinocerotidae. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle C, 4, 16: 81 - 95." type="journal article" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FD2FCE7AFCF4FE8E" author="GIAOURTSAKIS I." box="[677,872,279,306]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="235 - 253" refId="ref19737" refString="GIAOURTSAKIS I. 2003. - Late Neogene Rhinocerotidae of Greece: distribution, diversity and stratigraphical range. Deinsea 10: 235 - 253" type="journal article" year="2003">Giaourtsakis 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FCF9CE7AFC30FE8E" author="GIAOURTSAKIS I." box="[883,940,279,306]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="157 - 187" refId="ref19762" refString="GIAOURTSAKIS I. 2009. - The Late Miocene Mammal Faunas of the Mytilinii Basin, Samos Island, Greece: new collection. 15. Rhinocerotidae. Beitrage zur Palaontologie 31: 157 - 187." type="journal article" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FC32CE7AFB2AFE8E" author="GIAOURTSAKIS I. &amp; THEODOROU G. &amp; ROUSSIAKIS S. &amp; NASSIOU A. &amp; ILIOPOULOS G." box="[952,1206,279,306]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="367 - 398" refId="ref19799" refString="GIAOURTSAKIS I., THEODOROU G., ROUSSIAKIS S., ATHA- NASSIOU A. &amp; ILIOPOULOS G. 2006. - Late Miocene horned rhinoceroses from Kerassia (Euboea, Greece). Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie Abhandlungen 239: 367 - 398." type="journal article" year="2006">
Giaourtsakis 
<emphasis id="B95AD64DFFB13D11FBC8CE75FBE9FE8D" box="[1090,1141,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF77AEFFB13D11FD2FCE5AFC2CFEEE" author="GERAADS D. &amp; SPASSOV N." box="[677,944,311,338]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" pagination="99 - 122" refId="ref19501" refString="GERAADS D. &amp; SPASSOV N. 2009. - Rhinocerotidae from the late Miocene of Bulgaria. Palaeontographica A, 287: 99 - 122." type="journal article" year="2009">Geraads &amp; Spassov 2009</bibRefCitation>
). At Str-2, the absence of upper incisors,and the presence of relatively large lower ones, suggest an age slightly earlier than Pikermi, if we are correct in assuming a trend towards reduction of the incisors.
</paragraph>
